Follow [docs/README_02_GAMEPLAY_VISUAL_UX_REPLAYABILITY.md](docs/README_02_GAMEPLAY_VISUAL_UX_REPLAYABILITY.md) §16–17.

**Always visible (Khan 1 minimum):** lives/gate, Gold, Sacred Fire, wave, pause, speed, hero portrait/HP/energy/skill, tower build cards, selected-tower context.

**Contextual (progressive disclosure):** cleanse, brazier, Morale/Farr expansion, Forge, repair/sell, objectives, boss phase — do not show every future system on first battle.

**Alert priority (high → low):** gate danger → tower hijack → regional collapse → boss telegraph → objective → wave update → reward.

**Layout (1920×1080 landscape, thumb zones):**

- Top left: lives, gold, Sacred Fire, wave
- Top right: pause, speed, settings/cleanse when relevant
- Bottom left: hero portrait and skill
- Bottom center: tower cards (four starters in slice)
- Bottom right: contextual tower action

Touch targets ~44×44 dp minimum; icons over long labels during waves. No baked text in image UI assets. Wire **touch** via InputMap/actions, not mouse-only. Do not block the battlefield with full-screen panels during active waves unless paused.

Pardeh Break: illustrated “page turn” feel — Fate choice + brief summary, not a heavy meta spreadsheet.
